        <!-- Slide 2: What is an AI Agent? -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h2>🤖 What Is an AI Agent?</h2>
            
            <div class="example-box">
                <h4>💬 Imagine This:</h4>
                <p><strong>You:</strong> "Plan a weekend trip to Goa."</p>
                <p><strong>AI Agent:</strong> "Done! I've found the best flights, hotels, and weather details. Here's your itinerary."</p>
            </div>

            <h3>What It Is:</h3>
            <p>An AI Agent is a smart digital assistant that can:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-points">
                <li>Understand your natural language</li>
                <li>Think and plan what to do</li>
                <li>Use tools (like a browser or calculator)</li>
                <li>Do tasks for you autonomously</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="workflow-box">
                <h4>Real-Life Examples:</h4>
                <ul class="bullet-points">
                    <li><strong>"Summarize this document"</strong> → Reads and summarizes it</li>
                    <li><strong>"Find cheapest flights to Mumbai"</strong> → Searches online</li>
                    <li><strong>"Write an email to my boss"</strong> → Drafts it using your tone</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 3: What is MCP? -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h2>📋 What Is MCP (Model Context Protocol)?</h2>
            
            <div class="example-box">
                <h4>💬 Imagine This:</h4>
                <p>You ask your AI Agent: <em>"Summarize this email and add it to the database."</em></p>
            </div>

            <div class="flow-diagram">
                <div class="flow-step">1. Clean Email</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">2. Summarize</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">3. Generate Embedding</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">4. Save to Database</div>
            </div>

            <h3>What It Is:</h3>
            <p>MCP is like a recipe or blueprint that tells your AI system:</p>
            <ul class="bullet-points">
                <li>What steps to follow</li>
                <li>What data to pass between steps</li>
                <li>What tools or models to call</li>
                <li>How to update or maintain memory (context)</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="analogy-box">
                <h4>🍳 Analogy:</h4>
                <p><strong>AI Agent</strong> = Chef | <strong>MCP</strong> = Recipe/Instructions | <strong>Tools</strong> = Knife, pan, ingredients</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 4: MCP Use Case -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h2>📋 MCP Use Case Example</h2>
            
            <h3>Customer Support Agent Workflow:</h3>
            
            <div class="flow-diagram" style="flex-direction: column; align-items: stretch;">
                <div class="flow-step" style="margin: 10px 0;">1. Detect Intent</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow" style="text-align: center;">↓</div>
                <div class="flow-step" style="margin: 10px 0;">2. Fetch Related Case</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow" style="text-align: center;">↓</div>
                <div class="flow-step" style="margin: 10px 0;">3. Summarize Conversation</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow" style="text-align: center;">↓</div>
                <div class="flow-step" style="margin: 10px 0;">4. Suggest Resolution</div>
            </div>

            <div class="workflow-box">
                <h4>Key Benefits of MCP:</h4>
                <ul class="bullet-points">
                    <li><strong>Standardization:</strong> Consistent workflow patterns</li>
                    <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> Easy to replicate and modify</li>
                    <li><strong>Memory Management:</strong> Maintains context across steps</li>
                    <li><strong>Tool Integration:</strong> Seamless connection between different services</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 5: What is LangGraph? -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h2>🔗 What Is LangGraph?</h2>
            
            <div class="example-box">
                <h4>💻 Imagine This:</h4>
                <p>You're a developer who wants to build the workflow using MCP principles.</p>
            </div>

            <h3>What It Is:</h3>
            <p>LangGraph is a Python framework to build <strong>stateful, multi-step AI workflows</strong>, inspired by the MCP pattern.</p>

            <h3>It lets you connect steps (nodes) in a graph. Each node can:</h3>
            <ul class="bullet-points">
                <li>Use an LLM (OpenAI or Gemini)</li>
                <li>Call tools (search, DB, embedding)</li>
                <li>Modify shared memory (state)</li>
            </ul>

            <div class="flow-diagram">
                <div class="flow-step">User Input</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">Fetch Emails</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">Clean Emails</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">Summarize</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">Embed</div>
                <div class="flow-arrow">→</div>
                <div class="flow-step">Store in Qdrant</div>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: center; font-style: italic; color: #667eea; margin-top: 20px;">
                Each step is a LangGraph node. The process uses MCP logic. The agent triggers the graph.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Slide 6: How They All Connect -->
        <div class="slide">
            <h2>🔄 How They All Connect</h2>
            
            <table class="comparison-table">
